All tests pass and `go vet` is clean. Here's a summary of what was implemented:

## Summary

### New files
- **`internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`** — Core orchestration loop with `Orchestrator` struct, `Run()`, `TriggerAll()`, `OnRunComplete()`, and `Register()` methods. Respects per-project concurrency limits, claims tasks, generates prompts, and dispatches workflow runs.
- **`internal/orchestrator/orchestrator_test.go`** — 12 tests covering: dispatch, concurrency limits, no slots, no tasks, unregistered project, prompt generation failure, dispatch failure, claim failure, trigger-all, on-run-complete, in-flight tracking, and workflow selection.
- **`internal/adapters/beads/tracker.go`** — Beads adapter implementing `ports.TaskTracker` backed by `.beads/issues.jsonl`. Reads JSONL (last-occurrence-wins, tombstone support), returns open tasks sorted by priority.
- **`internal/adapters/beads/tracker_test.go`** — 9 tests covering: empty, filtering, last-occurrence-wins, tombstones, claim/complete/fail, not-found.

### Modified files
- **`internal/config/config.go`** — Added `OrchestrationConfig` struct (enabled, tracker, concurrency, workflow) with defaults (beads, 1, develop).
- **`internal/config/config_test.go`** — Added 2 tests for orchestration config loading and defaults.
- **`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** — Added `OnRunCompleteFunc` callback, `SetOnRunComplete()`, `SetOrchestrateFunc()`, `Orchestrate()` RPC handler, and fires the callback after each run completes.
- **`cmd/cloched/main.go`** — Wires up orchestrator: creates it from project config, registers the beads tracker, sets up dispatch function via `srv.RunWorkflow`, connects on-run-complete callback, Orchestrate RPC, and triggers on startup.
- **`api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`** — Added `Orchestrate` RPC with `OrchestrateRequest`/`OrchestrateResponse` messages.
- **`api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go`**, **`api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go`** — Regenerated from proto.

### Acceptance criteria met
1. Orchestrator triggers on startup, run completion, and manual `Orchestrate` RPC
2. Respects per-project concurrency limits (tracked in-memory)
3. Claims tasks, generates prompts via LLM, dispatches runs
4. Tests cover orchestration logic (12 orchestrator tests, 9 beads tests, 2 config tests)

